3. Database Overview
- What are databases?
  + store and organize data
  + useful dealing with large amount of data
- Why use databases?
  + speadsheets vs databases
    table: rows and columns
- Platform: 
  + postgreSQL
  + MySQL
  + SQL Server
  + others ...
- SQL : a language used to manipulate database, same for many platform

4. Install pgadmin
- What? GUI 
- For this course: pgAdmin 3
- Installer: https://www.postgresql.org/download/
- Windows installers
- Interactive installer by EnterpriseDB
- Password: root 
- Port: 5432 (Default)
- Locale: Default
- Uncheck last option
- Run pgAdmin, enter password
- Create new blank database named 'dvdrental'. Save
- Configure PostgreSQL binary path: 
  + File -> Preferences -> Path -> Binary Path
  + C:\Program Files\PostgreSQL\9.6\bin -> To restore db from file and some other utilities
- dvdrental -> Restore -> Link to file .tar -> Refresh -> Ready to go
- Try some first queries
- Done 
